// services/run_server.lang — GLang HTTP "run" service for the learn platform.
//
// POST /api/run  { "source": "<glang program>" }
//   -> { ok, output:[...lines], stderr, exit, diagnostics?:[{line,col,message}] }
// GET  /healthz -> "ok"
//
// Runs untrusted code IN-PROCESS through the real interpreter, so it supports
// the full language including `std/` imports (resolved by the loader against
// --stdlib at runtime). Safety:
//   * the Interp is given a finite step + call-depth budget (--max-steps), so an
//     infinite loop or runaway recursion terminates with a clean error;
//   * an app-layer guard rejects programs that name the raw filesystem builtins;
//   * Docker provides the real backstop (read-only rootfs, mem/cpu limits, no
//     network egress, non-root) — see the compose file.
//
// Single-threaded poll loop (std/server.lang): one request runs at a time, which
// is why a single reused temp filename is safe. The execution body is isolated
// in runPipeline()/executeSource() so a subprocess-per-request executor can
// replace the in-process call later without touching the HTTP contract.
//
// Build (from toolchain/):
//   ./glangc services/run_server.lang services/run_server.c
//   gcc -O2 -w services/run_server.c runtime/glang_runtime.c -o services/run_server
//   ./services/run_server --port 8081 --stdlib stdlib --tmp /tmp --max-steps 5000000

